# AWS Environment — Terraform

This repository manages the full AWS environment using Terraform.
All existing resources are imported gradually, phase by phase.

## Structure

```
aws-environment/
├── environments/
│   └── prod/               # Production environment (consumer of modules)
│       ├── main.tf         # Calls all modules
│       ├── variables.tf    # Input variables
│       ├── locals.tf       # Common tags and naming
│       ├── outputs.tf      # Environment-level outputs
│       └── terraform.tfvars# Actual variable values (gitignored)
│
├── modules/                # Reusable resource modules
│   ├── vpc/                # VPC, subnets, IGW, route tables
│   ├── security_groups/    # All security groups
│   ├── iam/                # IAM roles, policies, instance profiles
│   ├── ec2/                # EC2 instances, EIPs, ENIs
│   ├── rds/                # RDS instances and subnet groups
│   ├── s3/                 # S3 buckets and policies
│   ├── alb/                # Load balancers, target groups, listeners
│   ├── route53/            # DNS hosted zones and records
│   └── cloudwatch/         # Alarms, log groups, dashboards
│
└── global/
    └── s3-backend/         # Remote state bucket + DynamoDB lock table
```

## Import Order (Phases)

| Phase | Module            | Status      |
|-------|-------------------|-------------|
| 1     | global/s3-backend | ⬜ Pending  |
| 2     | vpc               | ✅ Complete |
| 3     | security_groups   | ✅ Complete |
| 4     | iam               | ✅ Complete |
| 5     | s3                | ✅ Complete |
| 6     | ec2               | ✅ Complete |
| 7     | rds               | ⏭ Skipped  |
| 8     | alb               | ⏭ Skipped  |
| 9     | route53           | ⏭ Skipped  |
| 10    | cloudwatch        | ✅ Complete |

## Usage

```bash
cd environments/prod
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
```

## Security Scanning

Run after every import phase:
```bash
checkov -d .
tfsec .
terraform validate
tflint
```
